com.mygdx.game

Class SplashScreen

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mygdx.game.SplashScreen
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.badlogic.gdx.Screen

    public class SplashScreen
extends java.lang.Object
implements com.badlogic.gdx.Screen
    The SplashScreen class shows an animation of the main character running across the screen with a boulder following, displaying the company name on the screen. Once the company name fades, the game is taken to the main menu.

    Instance Variables

    batch Instance of SpriteBatch that allows for elements to display on the screen.

    game Instance of MainGame that allows for screen changes.

    walkAnim Instance of Animation that allows for animation of walking frames.

    rollAnim Instance of Animation that allows for animation of rolling frames.

    framesWalk Array of TextureRegion that contains the frames for walk animation.

    framesRoll Array of TextureRegion that contains the frames for roll animation.

    splashTitleSprite Instance of Sprite that loads the sprite for the company title.

    walk Instance of Texture that loads the spritesheet for walk animation.

    roll Instance of Texture that loads the spritesheet for roll animation.

    background Instance of Texture that loads the background image.

    splashTitle Instance of Texture that loads the splashscreen image.

    time Float variable used to keep track of time for animation.

    speed Float variable used to determine speed of animation.

    walkX Float variable used to determine the user's location.

    tweenManager Instance of TweenManager used to animate the text.

    Version:
    3.0.0 26/05/2016
    Author:
    Brian Tran

    • Method Detail

      • show

        public void show()
        The show method is used to initialize all of the variables, as well as set all the positions, and sizes for each of the sprites to be drawn on screen. The show method runs every time the application is ran.
        Specified by:
        show in interface com.badlogic.gdx.Screen

      • render

        public void render(float delta)
        The render() method is an overridden method from the GDX library. The render method is run every frame, and as a result, updates the screen every frame with new information. This allows for animations of sprites and such to be easier. Things are displayed on the screen using a SpriteBatch, which acts as a container of sorts for the screen elements.Various for loops are used to detect user input, as for collision and detection.
        Specified by:
        render in interface com.badlogic.gdx.Screen
